TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Accumulation chart is a Data visualization component which is divided into slices to represent the given numerical values.
            In this each slice represents its corresponding numerical value.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The accumulation chart control is used to visualize the data in the different types of graphical representations with built-in features like Grouping, legends, tooltip, and more.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the chart, which accepts data in hex, rgba as a valid CSS color string.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: BackgroundImage
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background image of the chart that accepts data in string as url link or location of an image.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataSource
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies the dataSource for the AccumulationChart. It can be an array of JSON objects or an instance of DataManager.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Query
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies Query to select data from dataSource. This property is applicable only when the dataSource is `Ej.DataManager`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataSourceChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when dataSource for the chart changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAnimation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set true, enables the animation for accumulation chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableBorderOnMouseMove
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set true, enables the border in pie chart while mouse moving.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableSmartLabels
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set true, labels for the point will be placed smartly without overlapping.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The height of the chart as a string in order to provide input as both like '100px' or '100%'.
            If specified as '100%, chart will render to the full height of its parent element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HighlightMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether point has to get highlighted or not. Takes chartItems either 'None 'or 'Point'.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HighlightPattern
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether series or data point has to be selected. They are,
            none: sets none as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            chessboard: sets chess board as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            dots: sets dots as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            diagonalForward: sets diagonal forward as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            crosshatch: sets crosshatch as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            pacman: sets pacman highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            diagonalbackward: sets diagonal backward as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            grid: sets grid as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            turquoise: sets turquoise as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            star: sets star as highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            triangle: sets triangle as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            circle: sets circle as highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            tile: sets tile as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            horizontaldash: sets horizontal dash as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            verticaldash: sets vertical dash as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            rectangle: sets rectangle as highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            box: sets box as highlighting pattern to accumulation chart.
            verticalstripe: sets vertical stripe as highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            horizontalstripe: sets horizontal stripe as highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            bubble: sets bubble as highlighting  pattern to accumulation chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsMultiSelect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set true, enables the multi selection in accumulation chart. It requires `SelectionMode` to be `Point`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectionMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether point has to get selected or not. Takes chartItems either 'None 'or 'Point'.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectionPattern
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            chessboard: sets chess board as selecting pattern accumulation chart .

            horizontaldash: sets horizontal dash as selecting pattern to accumulation chart.

            rectangle: sets rectangle as selecting pattern.
            box: sets box as selecting pattern to accumulation chart.
            verticalstripe: sets vertical stripe as  selecting pattern to accumulation chart.

            </summary>

             Chart - Annotation renders based on chart coordinates.
             Series - Annotation renders based on series coordinates.

<summary>

            else is specifies pixel or percentage of coordinate.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of horizontal axis associated with the annotation.
            It requires `Axes` of chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Y
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            if set coordinateUnit as `Pixel` Y specifies the axis value
            else is specifies pixel or percentage of coordinate.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: YAxisName
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of vertical axis associated with the annotation.
            It requires `Axes` of chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies indexed category  axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsInversed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It specifies whether the axis to be rendered in inversed manner or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Unique identifier of an axis.
            To associate an axis with the series, set this name to the xAxisName/yAxisName properties of the series.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OpposedPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the axis will render at the opposite side of its default position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the title of an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of data the axis is handling.
            Double:  Renders a numeric axis.
            DateTime: Renders a dateTime axis.
            Category: Renders a category axis.
            Logarithmic: Renders a log axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, axis label will be visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Coefficient
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The polar radar radius position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColumnIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the index of the column where the axis is associated,
            when the chart area is divided into multiple plot areas by using `Columns`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrossesAt
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value at which the axis line has to be intersect with the vertical axis or vice versa.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrossesInAxis
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies axis name with which the axis line has to be crossed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Description
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Description for axis and its element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DesiredIntervals
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            With this property, you can request axis to calculate intervals approximately equal to your specified interval.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EdgeLabelPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of labels at the edge of the axis.They are,
             None: No action will be performed.
             Hide: Edge label will be hidden.
             Shift: Shifts the edge labels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAutoIntervalOnZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, axis interval will be calculated automatically with respect to the zoomed range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableScrollbarOnZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables the scrollbar for zooming.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTrim
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Trim property for an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IntervalType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the types like `Years`, `Months`, `Days`, `Hours`, `Minutes`, `Seconds` in date time axis.They are,
            Auto: Defines the interval of the axis based on data.
            Years: Defines the interval of the axis in years.
            Months: Defines the interval of the axis in months.
            Days: Defines the interval of the axis in days.
            Hours: Defines the interval of the axis in hours.
            Minutes: Defines the interval of the axis in minutes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Interval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the interval for an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Minimum
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the minimum range of an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the placement of a label for category axis. They are,
            betweenTicks: Renders the label between the ticks.
            onTicks: Renders the label on the ticks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Maximum
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum range of an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZoomFactor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The axis is scaled by this factor. When zoomFactor is 0.5, the chart is scaled by 200% along this axis. Value ranges from 0 to 1.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZoomPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Position of the zoomed axis. Value ranges from 0 to 1.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelFormat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Used to format the axis label that accepts any global string format like 'C', 'n1', 'P' etc.
            It also accepts placeholder like '{value}C' in which value represent the axis label, e.g, 20C.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelIntersectAction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the actions like `None`, `Hide`, `Trim`, `Wrap`, `MultipleRows`, `Rotate45`, and `Rotate90`
            when the axis labels intersect with each other.They are,
            None: Shows all the labels.
            Hide: Hides the label when it intersects.
            Trim: Trim the label when it intersects.
            Wrap: Wrap the label when it intersects.
            MultipleRows: Shows the label in MultipleRows when it intersects.
            Rotate45: Rotates the label to 45 degree when it intersects.
            Rotate90: Rotates the label to 90 degree when it intersects.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelPadding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the labelPadding from axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Name: RangePadding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the padding for the axis range in terms of interval.They are,
            none: Padding cannot be applied to the axis.
            normal: Padding is applied to the axis based on the range calculation.
            additional: Interval of the axis is added as padding to the minimum and maximum values of the range.
            round: Axis range is rounded to the nearest possible value divided by the interval.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelIntersectAction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the actions like `None`, `Hide`, `Trim`, `Wrap`, `MultipleRows`, `Rotate45`, and `Rotate90`
            when the axis labels intersect with each other.They are,
            None: Shows all the labels.
            Hide: Hides the label when it intersects.
            Trim: Trim the label when it intersects.
            Wrap: Wrap the label when it intersects.
            MultipleRows: Shows the label in MultipleRows when it intersects.
            Rotate45: Rotates the label to 45 degree when it intersects.
            Rotate90: Rotates the label to 90 degree when it intersects.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.ChartZoomSettings
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options to customize the zoom settings of the chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableDeferredZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             If set to true, zooming will be performed on mouse up. It requires `EnableSelectionZooming` to be true.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMouseWheelZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, chart can be zoomed by using mouse wheel.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePan
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether chart needs to be panned by default.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePinchZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If to true, chart can be pinched to zoom in / zoom out.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableScrollbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether axis needs to have scrollbar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableSelectionZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, chart can be zoomed by a rectangular selecting region on the plot area.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to allow zooming vertically or horizontally or in both ways. They are,
            x,y: Chart can be zoomed both vertically and horizontally.
            x: Chart can be zoomed horizontally.
            y: Chart can be zoomed  vertically.
            It requires `EnableSelectionZooming` to be true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolbarItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the toolkit options for the zooming as follows:
            Zoom
            ZoomIn
            ZoomOut
            Pan
            Reset.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Buttons.SfButton
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The Button is a graphical user interface element that triggers an event on its click action.
            It can contain a text, an image, or both.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets content for button element including HTML and its customizations.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the text content of the button element and it will support only string type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines class/multiple classes separated by a space in the button element. The Button types, styles, and
            size can be defined by using this property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether the Button is enabled or disabled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering Button component in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconCss
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines class/multiple classes separated by a space for the Button that is used to include an icon.
            Buttons can also include font icon and sprite image.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Positions the icon based on the text content in the button and its default value is Left.
            The possible values are:
            - Left: The icon will be positioned to the left of the text content.
            - Right: The icon will be positioned to the right of the text content.
            - Top: The icon will be positioned to the top of the text content.
            - Bottom: The icon will be positioned to the bottom of the text content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsPrimary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows the appearance of the button to be enhanced and visually appealing when set to true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsToggle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Makes the Button toggle, when set to true. When you click it, the state changes from normal to active or viceversa.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<exclude />
            <summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as id, title etc., to the button element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when button element is clicked.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Created
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers once the component rendering is completed.
            </summary>

In the below code example, a basic Signature component initialized with tag directive. ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinStrokeWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the minimum stroke width for signature. 
            The <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component calculates stroke width based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.Velocity" />, <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MinStrokeWidth" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MaxStrokeWidth" />.
            </summary>
            <value>

            </value>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the maximum stroke width for signature.
            The <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature" /> component calculates stroke width based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.Velocity" />, <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MinStrokeWidth" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MaxStrokeWidth" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            The maximum width of stroke. The default value is <c>2.0</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Velocity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the velocity to calculate the stroke thickness based on the pressure of the contact on the digitizer surface.
            The Signature component calculates stroke thickness based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.Velocity" />, <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MinStrokeWidth" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSignature.MaxStrokeWidth" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            The velocity to calculate the stroke thickness based on the pressure of the contact on the digitizer surface. The default value is <c>0.7</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to persist component's state between page reloads.
            </summary>

            <c>true</c>, if the component's state persistence is enabled. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            Component's property will be stored in browser local storage to persist component's state when page reloads.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSlider<TValue>
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>
            <typeparam name="TValue">Generic type parameter.</typeparam>.
            <summary>
            The Slider component allows the user to select a value or range of values
            in-between the min and max range, by dragging the handle over the slider bar.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the partial class SfSlider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the type of the type parameter TValue for the Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfSlider<TValue> component.

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets id attribute for the slider element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the ChildContent.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueExpression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expression for defining the value of the bound.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom classes to be added to the element used to customize the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CustomValues
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies an array of slider values in number or string type.
            The min and max step values are not considered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAnimation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables/Disables the animation for slider movement.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable persisting component's state between page reloads.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables or disables the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Max
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum value of the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Min
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the minimum value of the slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Orientation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies whether to render the slider in vertical or horizontal orientation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReadOnly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the render the slider in read-only mode to restrict any user interaction.
            The slider rendered with user defined values and cant be interacted with user actions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowButtons
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to show or hide the increase/decrease buttons
            of Slider to change the slider value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Step
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the step value for each value change when the increase / decrease
             button is clicked or on arrow keys press or on dragging the thumb.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the type of the Slider. The available options are:
              Default - Allows to a single value in the Slider.
              MinRange - Allows to select a single value in the Slider. It displays a shadow from the start to the current value.
              Range - Allows to select a range of values in the Slider. It displays shadow in-between the selection range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It is used to denote the current value of the Slider.
            The value should be specified in array of number when render Slider type as range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Slider.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsImmediateValue
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the value need to be updated at the time of dragging slider handle.
            </summary>

<summary>
            The TextBox is an input element that allows to get input from the user. It allows the user to edit or display the text value.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The TextBox is an input element that allows to get input from the user. It allows the user to edit or display the text value.
            </summary>

            </summary>

            The TextBox is an input element that allows to get input from the user. It allows the user to edit or display the text value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Blur
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the TextBox has focus-out.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the content of TextBox has changed and gets focus-out.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Created
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the TextBox component is created.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Destroyed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the TextBox component is destroyed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Focus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the TextBox gets focus.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Input
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers each time when the value of TextBox has changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Autocomplete
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the browser is allowed to automatically enter or select a value for the TextBox.
            <para>By default, autocomplete is enabled for TextBox.</para>
            <para>Possible values are:</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>On</term>
            <description>Specifies that autocomplete is enabled</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Off</term>
            <description>Specifies that autocomplete is disabled.</description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FloatLabelType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the floating label behavior of the TextBox that the placeholder text floats above the TextBox based on the following values.
            <para>Possible values are:</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Never</term>
            <description>Never floats the label in the TextBox when the placeholder is available.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Always</term>
            <description>The floating label always floats above the TextBox.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Auto</term>
            <description>The floating label floats above the TextBox after focusing it or when enters the value in it.</description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Placeholder
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the boolean value whether the TextBox allows user to change the text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Readonly
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the boolean value whether the TextBox allows user to change the text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowClearButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the clear button is displayed in TextBox.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the TextBox component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the tab order of the TextBox component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Multiline
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that enables or disables the multiline on the TextBox.
            The TextBox changes from a single line to multiline when enabling this multiline mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as styles, class, and more to the root element.
            If you configured both property and equivalent html attributes, then the component considers the property value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            If you configured both property and equivalent input attribute, then the component considers the property value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the behavior of the TextBox such as text, password, email, and more.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnChange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the content of input has changed and gets focus-out.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnInput
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers each time when the value of input has changed.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnPaste
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the content is paste into an input.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnBlur
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the input has focus-out.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: OnFocus
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the input gets focus.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the id of the TextBox component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Value
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the content of the TextBox.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the callback to trigger when the value changes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueExpression
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expression for defining the value of the bound.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS class name that can be appended with the root element of the TextBox. One or more custom CSS classes can be added to a TextBox.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the persisting TextBox state between page reloads. If enabled, the `Value` state will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in the right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the TextBox allows the user to interact with it.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValidateOnInput
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the component validates the input or not. true, If the ValidateOnInput is enabled for form validation, then the model value will be updated on entering the value to the input. otherwise, false.The default value is false. This property is used to validate the form on typing into the input and updating the model value. The ValueChange event will be fired after the component lost its focus.

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Inputs.SfUploader
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The uploader component is useful to upload images, documents, and other files to server.
            The component is the extended version of HTML5 that is uploaded with multiple file selection, auto upload, drag and drop, progress bar, preload files, and validation.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the list of files that will be preloaded on rendering of uploader component.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Specifies the list of files that will be preloaded on rendering of uploader component.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            The uploader component is useful to upload images, documents, and other files to server.
            The component is the extended version of HTML5 that is uploaded with multiple file selection, auto upload, drag and drop, progress bar, preload files, and validation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the id of the Uploader component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the content that has to be passed.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowedExtensions
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the extensions of the file types allowed in the Uploader component and pass the extensions
            with comma separators.
            <para> For example,if you want to upload specific image files, pass `AllowedExtensions` as ".jpg,.png".</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AutoUpload
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            By default, the Uploader component initiates automatic upload when the files are added in upload queue.
            <para>If you want to manipulate the files before uploading to server, disable the AutoUpload property.</para>
            <para>The buttons "upload" and "clear" will be hided from file list when AutoUpload property is true.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS class name that can be appended with root element of the Uploader.
            One or more custom CSS classes can be added to a Uploader.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DirectoryUpload
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the folder of files can be browsed in the Uploader component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DropArea
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the drop target to handle the drag-and-drop upload.
            By default, the Uploader creates wrapper around file input that will act as drop target.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DropEffect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the drag operation effect to the Uploader component.
            <para> Possible values are .</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Copy</term>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Move</term>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Link</term>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>None</term>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable persisting Uploader state between page reloads. If enabled, the `Files` state will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering Uploader in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the Uploader allows the user to interact with it.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>You can add the additional html attributes such as styles, class, and more to the root element.</para>
            <para>If you configured both property and equivalent html attributes, then the component considers the property value.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            If you configured both property and equivalent input attribute, then the component considers the property value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxFileSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum allowed file size to be uploaded in bytes.
            The property used to make sure that you cannot upload too large files.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinFileSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the minimum file size to be uploaded in bytes.
            The property used to make sure that you cannot upload empty files and small files.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowMultiple
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the multiple files can be browsed or dropped simultaneously in the Uploader component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SequentialUpload
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            By default, the file Uploader component is processing the multiple files simultaneously.
            <para>If SequentialUpload property is enabled, the file upload component performs the upload one after the other.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowFileList
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the default file list can be rendered.
            The property used to prevent default file list and design own template for file list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the tab order of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the HTML string that used to customize the content of each file in the list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnChange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the content of input has changed and gets focus-out.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

            By default, the Uploader component initiates automatic upload when the files are added in upload queue.
            <para>If you want to manipulate the files before uploading to server, disable the AutoUpload property.</para>
            <para>The buttons "upload" and "clear" will be hided from file list when AutoUpload property is true.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CSS class name that can be appended with root element of the Uploader.
            One or more custom CSS classes can be added to a Uploader.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DirectoryUpload
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the folder of files can be browsed in the Uploader component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DropArea
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the drop target to handle the drag-and-drop upload.
            By default, the Uploader creates wrapper around file input that will act as drop target.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DropEffect
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the drag operation effect to the Uploader component.
            <para> Possible values are .</para>
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>Copy</term>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Move</term>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>Link</term>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>None</term>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable persisting Uploader state between page reloads. If enabled, the `Files` state will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering Uploader in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Enabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the Uploader allows the user to interact with it.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            <para>You can add the additional html attributes such as styles, class, and more to the root element.</para>
            <para>If you configured both property and equivalent html attributes, then the component considers the property value.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InputAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            If you configured both property and equivalent input attribute, then the component considers the property value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxFileSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum allowed file size to be uploaded in bytes.
            The property used to make sure that you cannot upload too large files.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MinFileSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the minimum file size to be uploaded in bytes.
            The property used to make sure that you cannot upload empty files and small files.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowMultiple
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the multiple files can be browsed or dropped simultaneously in the Uploader component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SequentialUpload
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            By default, the file Uploader component is processing the multiple files simultaneously.
            <para>If SequentialUpload property is enabled, the file upload component performs the upload one after the other.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowFileList
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a boolean value that indicates whether the default file list can be rendered.
            The property used to prevent default file list and design own template for file list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the tab order of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the HTML string that used to customize the content of each file in the list.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnChange
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the content of input has changed and gets focus-out.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChunkSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the ChunkSize to split the large file into chunks, and upload it to the server in a sequential order.
            <para>If the ChunkSize property has value, the Uploader enables the chunk upload by default.
            It must be specified in bytes value.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RemoveUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the URL of remove action that receives the file information and handle the remove operation in server.
            <para>The remove action type must be POST request and define "RemoveFileNames" attribute to get file information that will be removed.
            This property is optional.</para>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RetryAfterDelay
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the delay time in milliseconds that the automatic retry happens after the delay.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RetryCount
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the number of retries that the Uploader can perform on the file failed to upload.
            By default, the Uploader set 3 as maximum retries. This property must be specified to prevent infinity looping.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SaveUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the URL of save action that will receive the upload files and save in the server.
            <para>The save action type must be POST request and define the argument as same input name used to render the component.
            The upload operations could not perform without this property.</para>
            </summary>

            </summary>

<summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnFileListRender
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers before rendering each file item from the file list in a page.
            It helps to customize specific file item structure.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Paused
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fires if pause the chunk file uploading.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Progressing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when uploading a file to the server using the AJAX request.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnRemove
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers on removing the uploaded file. The event used to get confirm before removing the file from server.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnResume
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Fires if resume the paused chunk file upload.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: FileSelected
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers after selecting or dropping the files by adding the files in upload queue.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Success
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the AJAX request gets success on uploading files or removing files.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnUploadStart
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the upload process gets started. This event is used to add additional parameter with upload request.
            </summary>

The aim is to make the user aware of their current position in a hierarchy of website links. Breadcrumb items can be populated either by specifying property or by specifying within tag directive. and can be used to customize the Breadcrumb component UI using tag directive. In the below code example, a basic Breadcrumb component initialized with tag directive. ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: ActiveItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets the of the active breadcrumb item. This property contains Url string of active breadcrumb item. This property is updated only when the has value. @code { private string activeItem = "https://blazor.syncfusion.com/demos/menu-bar/default-functionalities"; } ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the maximum number of breadcrumb items to be visible in the breadcrumb component.
            If the number of items exceeds this count, then items are rendered based on <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.OverflowMode" /> property. 
            </summary>
            <value>
            The number of breadcrumb items to be visible in breadcrumb component. The default value is <c>0</c>. 
            </value>
            <remarks>
            The <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.MaxItems" /> is applicable only if the number of <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.BreadcrumbItem" /> is greater than <c>2</c>.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: OverflowMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a value that indicates how to display breadcrumb items when the breadcrumb items count exceeds <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.MaxItems" />.
            </summary>
            <value>
            One of the <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.BreadcrumbOverflowMode" /> enumeration. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.BreadcrumbOverflowMode.Menu" />
            </value>
            <remarks>
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Hidden</c>, the exceeded items will be hidden and while clicking on the previous item, the hidden item will become visible.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Collapsed</c>,  only the first and last items will be visible, and the remaining items will be hidden with collapsed icon.
            When the collapsed icon is clicked, all items become visible and scroll will be enabled if the space is not enough to show all items. 
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Menu</c>, it shows the number of breadcrumb items that can be accommodated within the container space, and creates a sub menu with the remaining items.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Wrap</c>, it wraps the items on multiple lines when the Breadcrumbs width exceeds the container space.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>Scroll</c>, it shows an HTML scroll bar when the Breadcrumbs width exceeds the container space.
            If the <c>OverflowMode</c> is <c>None</c>, it shows all the items on a single line.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableNavigation
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets whether the built-in item navigation is enabled or not. The breadcrumb component navigates to url based on the item clicked by user. true, if built-in item navigation is enabled; otherwise, false.The default value is true. You can handle navigation in using event by setting as false.

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableActiveItemNavigation
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Gets or sets whether the navigation is enabled for active item (last breadcrumb item). true, if the navigation is enabled for last breadcrumb item and it is clickable. otherwise, false.The default value is false.

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to persist component's state between page reloads. When set to <c>true</c>, the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.ActiveItem" /> property is persisted.
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the component's state persistence is enabled. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            Component's <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfBreadcrumb.ActiveItem" /> property will be stored in browser local storage to persist component's state when page reloads.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether the right to left direction is enabled for breadcrumb component.
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the right to left direction is enabled for breadcrumb component. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether the breadcrumb component is disabled or not.
            </summary>
            <value>
            <c>true</c>, if the breadcrumb component is disabled. The default value is <c>false</c>.
            </value>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfSidebar
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The SfSidebar component is an expandable and collapsible component that typically acts as a side container to place primary or secondary content alongside the main content.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Partial Class SfSidebar.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Partial Class SfSidebar.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Partial Class SfSidebar.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Partial Class SfSidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Changed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the state(expand/collapse) of the component is changed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClose
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component is ready to close.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Created
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component is created.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Destroyed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component gets destroyed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Triggers when the component is ready to open.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets id attribute for the sidebar element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the child content.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the animation transitions on expanding or collapsing the Sidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CloseOnDocumentClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether the Sidebar needs to be closed or not when the document area is clicked.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DockSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the size of the Sidebar in dock state. Dock size can be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableDock
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the docking state of the component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableGestures
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables the expand or collapse while swiping in the touch devices.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable the persisting component's state between page reloads. If enabled, isOpen state will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering Sidebar in right to left direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsOpen
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the Sidebar component is open or close.
            When the Sidebar type is set to `Auto`,
            the component will be expanded in the desktop and collapsed in the mobile mode regardless of the isOpen property.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsOpenChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MediaQuery
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the media query string for resolution, when opens the Sidebar.
            Example: assigning media query value to '(min-width: 600px)' will open the sidebar component only when the provided resolution is met else the sidebar will be in closed state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of the Sidebar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowBackdrop
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to apply overlay options to the main content or not when the Sidebar is in an open state.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Target
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Allows to place the sidebar inside the target element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expanding types of the Sidebar.
            `Over` - The sidebar floats over the main content area.
            `Push` - The sidebar pushes the main content area to appear side-by-side and shrinks the main content within the screen width.
            `Slide` - The sidebar translates the x and y positions of the main content area based on the sidebar width.
            The main content area will not be adjusted within the screen width.
             `Auto` - Sidebar with `Over` type in mobile resolution and `Push` type in other higher resolutions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Sidebar. By default, the width of the Sidebar sets based on the size of its content.
            Width can also be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the z-index of the Sidebar. It is applicable only when sidebar act as the overlay type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            </summary>

<summary>
            Allows to place the sidebar inside the target element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the expanding types of the Sidebar.
            `Over` - The sidebar floats over the main content area.
            `Push` - The sidebar pushes the main content area to appear side-by-side and shrinks the main content within the screen width.
            `Slide` - The sidebar translates the x and y positions of the main content area based on the sidebar width.
            The main content area will not be adjusted within the screen width.
             `Auto` - Sidebar with `Over` type in mobile resolution and `Push` type in other higher resolutions.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Sidebar. By default, the width of the Sidebar sets based on the size of its content.
            Width can also be set in pixel values.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the z-index of the Sidebar. It is applicable only when sidebar act as the overlay type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional input attributes such as disabled, value, and more to the root element.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfTab
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>
            <summary>
            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>

            Tab is a content panel to show multiple contents in a compact space. Also, only one tab is active at a time. Each Tab item has an associated content, that will be displayed based on the active Tab.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ID
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets ID attribute for the tab element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Child Content for Tab.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Animation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the animation settings of the Tabs component. The animation effect can be applied to activate the tab with duration and delay.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets the CSS classes to the root element of the Tabs that helps to customize the component styles.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePersistence
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable persisting component's state between page reloads.
            If enabled, the tabs selected item will be persisted.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AllowDragAndDrop
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Indicates whether the Tab allows drag and drop over tab items. Tab item has been reordered based on the dropped item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DragArea
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the area in which the draggable element movement will be occurring. Outside that area will be restricted
            for the draggable element movement. By default, the draggable element movement occurs with Tabitems.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRtl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enable or disable rendering component in the right to left (RTL) direction.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HeaderPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the orientation of the Tab header.
            The possible values are:
            - Top: Places the Tab header on the top.
            - Bottom: Places the Tab header at the bottom.
            - Left: Places the Tab header at the left.
            - Right: Places the Tab header at the right.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the height of the Tabs component. By default, Tab height is set based on the height of its parent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Items
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A list of items that are used to configure the Tabs component.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LoadOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the modes for the Tab content.
            The possible modes are:
            `Dynamic` Load the Tab content dynamically, which is rendering its content when switching its header.
            `Init` Loads all the tab contents on initial loading.
            `Demand` Loads the Tab content when required but keeps the content once it is rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Locale
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Overrides the global culture and localization value for this component. Default global culture is 'en-US'.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OverflowMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the display mode which will be applied when the Tabs exceeds the viewing area.
            The possible modes are:
            - Scrollable: All the elements will be displayed in a single line with horizontal scrolling enabled.
            - Popup: Tab container will hold the items that can be placed within the available space and the rest of the items will be moved to the popup.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ScrollStep
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the scrolling distance that applies when scrolling in Tab and enabled Scrollable mode.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItem
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the index for activating the Tab item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SelectedItemChanged
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets a callback of the bound value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowCloseButton
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies a value that indicates whether to show the close button in the Tab header or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ReorderActiveTab
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to re-order tab items to show active tab item in the header area or popup when OverflowMode is Popup.
            </summary>
            <value>
            true, if active tab item should be visible in header area instead of pop-up; otherwise, false. The default value is true.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Navigations.SfTab.ReorderActiveTab" /> Property is only applicable when OverflowMode is popup.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Tabs component. By default, Tab width sets based on the width of its parent.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            You can add the additional html attributes such as id, title etc., to the tab element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IconPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options for positioning the icon in the Tab item header. This property depends on the `IconCss` property.
            The possible values are:
            - left: Places the icon to the `left` of the item.
            - top: Places the icon on the `top` of the item.
            - right: Places the icon to the `right` end of the item.
            - bottom: Places the icon at the `bottom` of the item.
            </summary>

<summary>
            Specifies the display text of the Tab header.

BoundAttributes.Name: OverflowMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Toolbar display mode when Toolbar content exceeds the viewing area.
            Possible modes are:
            - Scrollable: All the elements are displayed in a single line with horizontal scrolling enabled.
            - Popup: Prioritized elements are displayed on the Toolbar and the rest of elements are moved to the popup.
            - MultiRow: Displays the overflow toolbar items as an in-line of a toolbar.
            - Extended: Hide the overflowing toolbar items in the next row.  Show the overflowing toolbar items when you click the expand icons.
            If the popup content overflows the height of the page, the rest of the elements will be hidden.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            An item object that is used to configure Toolbar commands.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Child Content for Toolbar item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OnClick
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Event triggers when click the toolbar item.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Align
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies the location for aligning Toolbar items on the Toolbar. Each command will be aligned according to the `Align` property.
             Possible values are:
             - Left: To align commands to the left side of the Toolbar.
             - Center: To align commands at the center of the Toolbar.
             - Right: To align commands to the right side of the Toolbar.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CssClass
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines single/multiple classes (separated by space) to be used for customization of commands.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Disabled
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether an item should be disabled or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HtmlAttributes
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines htmlAttributes used to add custom attributes to Toolbar command.
            Supports HTML attributes such as style, class, etc.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Id
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the unique ID to be used with button or input element of Toolbar items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Overflow
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Toolbar command display area when an element's content is too large to fit available space.
            This is applicable only to `Popup` mode. Possible values are:
            - Show:  Always shows the item as the primary priority on the Toolbar.
            - Hide: Always shows the item as the secondary priority on the popup.
            - None: No priority for display, and as per normal order moves to popup when content exceeds.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: PrefixIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines single/multiple classes separated by space used to specify an icon for the button.
            The icon will be positioned before the text content if text is available, otherwise the icon alone will be rendered.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowAlwaysInPopup
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the priority of items to display it in popup always.
            It allows to maintain toolbar item on popup always but it does not work for toolbar priority items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowTextOn
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies where the button text will be displayed on popup mode of the Toolbar.
            Possible values are:
            - Toolbar:  Text will be displayed on Toolbar only.
            - Overflow: Text will be displayed only when content overflows to popup.
            - Both: Text will be displayed on popup and Toolbar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: SuffixIcon
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines single/multiple classes separated by space used to specify an icon for the button.
            The icon will be positioned after the text content if text is available.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Specifies the HTML element/element ID as a string that can be added as a Toolbar command.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Text
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the text to be displayed on the Toolbar button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TooltipText
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the text to be displayed on hovering the Toolbar button.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Type
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the types of command to be rendered in the Toolbar.
            Supported types are:
            - Button: Creates the Button control with its given properties like text, prefixIcon, etc.
            - Separator: Adds a horizontal line that separates the Toolbar commands.
            - Input: Creates an input element that is applicable to template rendering with Syncfusion controls like DropDownList,
            AutoComplete, etc.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether an item should be hidden or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the width of the Toolbar button commands.
            </summary>
